* Opal 2.3 release
  * Removal of number of CPUs for non-parallel jobs on input form
  * PBS support (with or without DRMAA)
  * Support upload of tarballs for inputs
  * Subset of wishlist below

* Utility services
  * Server load, queue length, data lifetime, server information

* Security enhancements
  * FacebookConnect or OpenID

* Plug-ins
  * Testing of Condor plug-in on RENCI's Condor pool
  * Hadoop/EC2 MapReduce plugin

* Performance improvements
  * Ability to queue jobs before job submission - based on an upper bound
    specified in opal.properties
  * Improved fault tolerance on server restart

* WSDL additions/improvements
  * Add GridFTP support
  * Additional statistics for job to be set by client (like email address)
    * Twitter, RSS access to job metadata
  * The <usage> tag is used improperly, it contains now the description of
    the application
  * launchJob should allow the user to specify the wallclock
  * REST support - and upgrade to Axis2
  * Support for array jobs
  * Support for hadoop jobs

* Additional Features
  * Addition of implicit files to dashboard 
    This will be in 2.something
  * Arguments schema: how to express 1-* or 2-* multiplicity? specify the
    min but not the max? LC
    Checked! We can express this condition simply using only the min tag 
    and not the max tag
  * Conditional display of parameters (a group of parameters are displayed only
    if a flag is checked) (reuqested by the PDB guys)
  * Display additional statistics on the dashboard - average load, queue
    time
    * May also need to provide programmatic access
  * Get the version of Opal 
  * Parameterize port numbers for dashboard

